__#📄Week 1 Summary (Python Basics – 200 Words)__

In Week 1, I learned the fundamentals of Python programming, which form the foundation for data processing and analysis. I studied basic concepts such as variables, data types (integers, floats, strings, and booleans), and operators used for performing arithmetic and logical operations. I also learned how to take input from users and display output using print statements.
I understood the importance of control structures like conditional statements (if-else), which help in decision-making, and loops (for and while), which allow repetition of tasks efficiently. These concepts helped me build logical thinking and problem-solving skills.
For hands-on practice, I implemented simple programs such as a temperature converter and basic calculator. These exercises improved my understanding of how Python works in real-life scenarios.
As part of the client project, I created a basic data processing script to calculate the average temperature from a list of values. This helped me understand how data can be stored, processed, and analyzed using Python.
Overall, this week provided me with a strong foundation in Python programming and prepared me for more advanced topics in data manipulation and analysis.
